<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ushintenshikurayami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shintenshi Kurayami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/17/01 6:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=166.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> *smirk*</span><hr size=1> Smirks, recognizing the elf he so not so long defeeated in battle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye. We have. I remember it clearly. You mocked my tactics...claiming blinding you with my magic and my use of a superior arnament dishonorable. If anyone should be bowing and begging...&quot; <br>
<br>
Smiles once again recalling the battle....<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
&quot;The attack on Kelethin has been succesfull! Flee, elves! Flee!! Hahah!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The only one who shall be fleeing is you, Dark Elf!&quot;<br>
<br>
His opponent turned and quickly, blades were drawn. The two charged into each other, firing off insults as often as spells. Metal rang upon metal, and soon the Dark Elf had fallen. Above him stood a smiling arrogant High Elf, already a viscious fire burned in his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where is your strength now? Where is your unholy might?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...if...if the circumstances were differant...&quot; The Teir'Dal choked on his blood that flowed up and out of his throat.<br>
<br>
&quot;You dishonor me!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That...weapon...is not ...yours...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I have fought by friends for days! weeks! months! I have payed for what I have with blood and tears! You have no room to talk! No room to judge me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I did not ask for you life story, elf. Your only lucky your gear is so go.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Gear? My weapon? You seem well off yourself, but perhaps I am mistaken. Fine then. I spare you, tonight...&quot;<br>
<br>
The high elf rumaged through his belongings, and upon finding what he sought, he tossed the Crystal Grinder at the feet of the Dark Elf.<br>
<br>
&quot;When next we meet, pray that you can drive that through my chest!&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that, The Paladin turnt and walked away. Slowly, his arrogance, hatred, and lust for battle ate away at his righteousness. Soon he would be lost in such visciousness. Such hostility. Such evil....<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I am the one you fought. I am Shintenshi Kurayami. Former Lifekeeper. You want to talk, then let us talk. But I bow to no mortal.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ukhasirath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khasirath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.violentharvest.com/sigs/vh_anim.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dire Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/17/01 7:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=166.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/khasface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *smirk*</span><hr size=1> Khasirath nods, his eyes betraying nothing of his feelings for that long off day. &quot;Indeed. I do not forget faces. I knew it was you. I hold that little momento still. We should go have that rematch you promised me. It will give us a chance to speak on what has brought one such as you to our door.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;In the meantime, go to the Library of the Grange, read on our rules. Pay close attention to those words about non-Teir'Dal known as Tillers and Harrowers. Should the Triad and Innoruuk be willing, know that that is the pinnacle of what you may become in our Order. Those not born as Innoruuk's children have their own seperate place within the Harvest.<br>
<br>
&quot;Should you have questions, seek me out. House S`Therik is easily found in the Third Gate of Neriak.&quot; He smirks a bit, a touch of true humor mixed with his sardonic nature, &quot;But should that be inconvenient, send a messanger, and I will meet you elsewhere.&quot; <p><center><a href="http://www.violentharvest.com"><img src="http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/khas_sig.jpg"></a><br>
